G″, characterizing the dissipated energy, and the phase angle
δ, distinguishing between elastic and viscous behavior66. Knowing the precise rheology is critical to understand how the product behaves during production, storage, and consumption70. By modulating any of these six rheological features, food scientists and food manufacturers can fine-tune the texture, consistency, and overall sensory appeal of the final product.
